<F P=100> NORTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   ROK's Kim, Delegation Conclude Meetings, Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   Trade Insurance Notes Exchanged </H4>
<F P=102> OW2503034794 Tokyo KYODO in English 0338 GMT 25 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2503034794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, March 25 KYODO -- Japan and South Korea 
exchanged notes in Tokyo on Friday [25 March] to promote mutual 
cooperation on trade insurance. Japan's Trade Minister Hiroshi 
Kumagai and his South Korean counterpart Kim chol-su agreed 
Thursday that the two countries will strive to build cooperative 
ties in government trade insurance. 
  Under the accord, Japan's Ministry of International Trade 
and 
Industry and Korea Export Insurance Corp. will jointly cover 
trade insurance for projects undertaken by Japanese and South 
Korean companies in developing countries. The cooperation will 
also feature regular meetings among insurance experts from the 
two countries and interchange of information on country risks 
and other problems involved in projects. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

