<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   DPRK `Moving' Nuclear Facilities Around Capital </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2603005794 Seoul CHOSON ILBO in Korean 26 Mar 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> SK2603005794 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul CHOSON ILBO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [AFP/YONHAP from Beijing] </F>
  [Text] On 25 March, one day before President Kim Yong-sam's 
China visit to seek China's active role in resolving the North 
Korean nuclear issue, nuclear experts in Beijing said North 
Korea is moving its nuclear facilities under suspicion through 
connecting underground passages to other places in Pyongyang. 
  Meanwhile, Beijing sources anticipate that, although 
President Kim will try to induce China to play an active role in 
resolving the North Korean nuclear issue during his five-day 
visit to China by using the ROK's economic strength, China will 
not immediately change its position on the issue. 

</TEXT>

