<H3> <TI>   Hata Calls EU's Brittan on Economic Package </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW3003050694 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database in Japanese 30 
Mar 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW3003050694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From MAINICHI SHIMBUN 30 March Morning Edition] </F>
  [Text] Deputy Prime Minister and Foreign Minister Tsutomu 
Hata telephoned Vice President of the European Union [EU] Leon 
Brittan on the evening of 29 March, to explain the substance of 
the external economic policy reform outline announced by the 
government on the same day. Regarding the economic package, 
Hata stressed this does not discriminate against any country in 
favor of the United States, and the economic measures were 
decided upon by the Japanese government on its own initiative to 
improve the people's quality of life. He is believed to have 
explained that the economic package is not for the sake of the 
United States, and sought the EU's understanding on this. 

</TEXT>

