<F P=103> OW3003100994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, March 30 KYODO -- The House of 
Representatives on Wednesday [30 March] approved a 50-day, 11.5 
trillion yen stopgap budget for fiscal 1994 and sent it 
immediately to the second chamber, the House of Councillors, for 
further deliberations. The upper chamber is expected to pass 
the provisional budget on Thursday, putting it into law, 
coalition sources said. 
  The stopgap budget will bridge a delay in Diet passage of 
the 
full fiscal 1994 budget of 73.08 trillion yen. 

