<F P=102>  OW2903054394 Tokyo KYODO in English 0510 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2903054394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, March 29 KYODO -- The coincident index of 
economic indicators for January stood at 85.0 percent, rising 
above the "boom-or-bust" 50 percent line for the first time in 
four months, the Economic Planning Agency said Tuesday [29 
March]. 
  The leading index, which projects economic conditions 
several 
months ahead, stood at 60.0 percent, showing improvement after 
staying below the 50 percent line for eight consecutive months, 
the agency said. 

