<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   SPA Spokesman: ROK Party Leader Visit Welcomed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2903152094 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1510 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2903152094 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["SPA Spokesman Hopes for Yi Ki-taek's Visit to Pyongyang"-- </F>
KCNA headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, March 29 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the 
Standing Committee of the Supreme People's Assembly (SPA) of the 
Democratic People's Republic of Korea released a statement today 
declaring that the invitation extended by the SPA chairman to 
president of the Democratic Party of South Korea Yi Ki-taek 
remains effective and expressing the hope that his visit to 
Pyongyang will surely be realised in a short time. 
  Recalling that SPA Chairman Yang Hyong-sop issued a 
statement 
on January 15 fully supporting the intention expressed by Yi 
Ki-taek at his New Year press conference to visit Pyongyang and 
meet with the great leader President Kim Il-song for the 
self-existence of the nation and the improvement of the 
North-South relations driven into a stalemate and that Yi 
Ki-taek reiterated his intention to visit the North on several 
official occasions, the spokesman says: 
  "We consider that his invariable intention to visit 
Pyongyang 
is an expression of patriotism out of the desire to break grave 
impasse at present and open a bright horizon for the nation. 
  "Anyone who is concerned over the destiny of the country and 
the nation must not block the will to visit Pyongyang and have a 
significant meeting with politicians but provide all necessary 
conditions and conveniences. 
  "We express the belief that his Pyongyang visit, if 
realised, 
would make an affirmative contribution to the denuclearization 
of the Korean peninsula, national reunification and other 
outstanding issues between the North and the South." 

</TEXT>

