<H3> <TI>   Expressions of Support Received From Abroad </TI></H3>
<H4>   From Cameroon, Lebanon, Russia </H4>
<F P=102> SK3003105294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1016 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK3003105294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Plot of United States and Its Followers Against DPRK </F>
Denounced" -- KCNA headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, March 30 (KCNA) -- Foreign party leaders 
and political parties strongly denounced the political plot of 
the United States and its followers against Korea. 
  Jean Pierre Ngambi, secretary general of the Communist Party 
of Cameroon, said on March 24 when he met the Korean ambassador 
that the anti-socialist campaign of the United States must be 
stopped, condemning the United States for totally reversing the 
agreed conclusions reached at the DPRK-U.S. contact in New York 
and leading the situation to the brink of a war. 
  Expressing the belief that the Korean people, firmly united 
behind His Excellency Kim Chong-il, supreme commander of the 
Korean People's Army, will win victory in confrontation with the 
enemy under his wise guidance, the secretary general stressed 
that the Communist Party of Cameroon would always support the 
Workers' Party of Korea in its struggle for realising the 
socialist cause and the reunification of the country. 
  Ali Hassan, general secretary of the Supreme Council of the 
Nationalist Socialist Party of Syria in Lebanon, in a statement 
on March 23 demanded that the unreasonable political plot of the 
United States and its followers against Korea be stopped at once. 
  He appealed to all the people who love justice and peace to 
wage a powerful solidarity movement for supporting the Korean 
people in their struggle to defend socialism centering on the 
popular masses. 
  A meeting of the presidium of the Central Executive 
Committee 
of the Federal Communist Party of Russia in a statement on March 
25 extended full support and solidarity to the struggle of the 
heroic Korean people united as firm as a rock around the 
Workers' Party of Korea. 

</TEXT>

