<H3> <TI>   Suharto Returns, Views G-15 New Delhi Summit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK3003090094 Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network in 
Indonesian 0600 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK3003090094 </F>
<F P=104>  Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Indonesian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President Suharto has said that the Group of 15 [G- 
15] wants to offer ideas or initiatives not only for the 
Nonaligned Movement [NAM] but also for enhancing South-South 
cooperation. Speaking to reporters aboard a DC-10 airliner 
flying home with the prsidential delegation, President Suharto 
said: 
  [Begin Suharto recording in progress] As I said earlier, the 
G-15 wants to offer ideas or initiatives on the selection of 
projects as a follow-up to NAM decisions. The G-15 is not only 
working for its own interests, but also wants to contribute 
ideas to NAM members through the NAM chairman as well as other 
South nations through the Group of 77. Thus, such ideas will 
serve the interests of both the NAM as well as enhance 
South-South cooperation. Various nations have made practical 
suggestions on the implementation of projects as a realization 
of South-South cooperation. I would like to say once again that 
not only will this serve the interests of the NAM itself, but it 
will also promote South-South cooperation. [end recording] 
  President Suharto and his delegation arrived at Halim 
Perdanakusuma Airport in Jakarta at 0930 West Indonesian 
Standard Time this morning from New Delhi. The president, who 
attended the G-15 summit in India from 28 to 30 March, was 
greeted by Vice President Try Sutrisno, ministers, and other 
senior officials at Halim Perdanakusuma Airport. 

</TEXT>

