<H3> <TI>   DPRK Envoy on Inspection-U.S. Talks Link </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK3003001594 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 2208 GMT 29 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK3003001594 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [REUTER/YONHAP from Vienna] </F>
  [Text] Kim Kwang-sop, North Korean ambassador to Austria, 
said today that North Korea will permit progress in the nuclear 
inspection [haek sacharul chinjonsikinun de tongui] only when 
the United States holds the third round of talks with it. 
  In an interview with REUTER, Ambassador Kim insisted that 
the 
best way to resolve the nuclear issue is to hold high-level 
talks between North Korea and the United States. 
  The third round of U.S.-North Korean talks was supposed to 
be 
held in Geneva last week but was canceled because North Korea 
did not allow the International Atomic Energy Agency inspection 
team to conduct an overall inspection of major nuclear 
facilities in Yongbyon. 

</TEXT>

