<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kim Il-song Reportedly Refused To Visit China </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2903232194 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 2210 GMT 29 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2903232194 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Yi Il-hwa from Tokyo] </F>
  [Text] Quoting Chinese sources, ASAHI SHIMBUN said in a 
report dispatched from Beijing today that North Korea's Kim 
Il-song will not visit China until the nuclear issue is resolved. 
  According to these sources, China understands that Kim 
Il-song has virtually refused to visit China. 
  In the opinion of the Beijing sources, Kim Il-song is wary 
of 
the possibility that China might claim credit if the nuclear 
issue were resolved after he visited China because it would seem 
to have been resolved due to China's persuasion. 

</TEXT>

