<H3> <TI>   DPRK Said To Upgrade Najin-Sonbong 
Trade Zone </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2703051494 Seoul TONG-A ILBO in Korean 27 Mar 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> SK2703051494 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul TONG-A ILBO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From NAEWOE News Agency] </F>
  [Text] It has been learned that North Korea has upgraded 
Najin-Sonbong area -- which was developed into a free economic 
trade zone in December 1991 -- into a direct-supervision city. 
The free economic trade zone, which has an area of 621 square 
km, will include some part of Undok County near the zone. As a 
result, the trade zone will have a total area of 764 square km. 

</TEXT>

