<H3> <TI>   Information Minister To Attend Security Meetings </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2503052294 Seoul YONHAP in English 0501 GMT 25 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2503052294 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, March 25 (YONHAP) -- Prime Minister Yi 
Hoe-chang instructed the information minister Friday to attend 
security-related and other important government meetings to make 
the administration's policies better known among the people, 
Information Minister O In-hwan said. 
  "In dealing with the North Korean nuclear problem, the 
intentions and direction of the government have not been fully 
delivered to the people, so it is necessary that the information 
minister attend some important meetings of cabinet ministers," 
Yi said as security-related ministers met at the prime 
minister's office. 
  "Under the past authoritarian governments, the Agency for 
National Security Planning led the way in explaining measures on 
North Korea and security, but now this is not proper under a 
civilian government," O said. He added that he will attend 
security-related meetings in the future and then provide 
detailed explanations on government measures and intentions on 
security matters. 

</TEXT>

