<F P=100> Philippines </F>
<H3> <TI>   Protest Against Arrest of Filipinos in Malaysia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK3003094194 Quezon City PTV-4 Television Network in Tagalog 
0500 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK3003094194 </F>
<F P=104>  Quezon City PTV-4 Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Tagalog </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Philippines has lodged a diplomatic protest 
with Malaysia in connection with the arrest by Malaysian 
authorities of some 1,000 Filipinos in Kuala Lumpur last Sunday. 
This was revealed by Alberto Encomienda, Philippine ambassador 
to Malaysia. 
  According to Encomienda, the arrested Filipinos are working 
in Kuala Lumpur. They were arrested and reportedly imprisoned 
by Malaysian authorities after attending a church service. The 
Filipino workers were arrested when they allegedly failed to 
present documentary evidence showing that their stay in Malaysia 
is legal. 

</TEXT>

