<F P=100> Thailand </F>
<H3> <TI>   Prasong, New Zealand Minister Discuss Trade </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK3003061694 Bangkok Radio Thailand Network in English 0000 
GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK3003061694 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok Radio Thailand Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Prasong Sunsiri has concluded his 
official visit to New Zealand as a guest of Deputy Prime 
Minister and Foreign Minister, Donald McKinnon. The visit 
during 24 to 27 March 1994 was aimed at enhancing cooperation, 
exchanging views on Asia-Pacific situation, and listening to 
opinions on ASEAN ministerial meeting hosted by Thailand in July 
this year. 
  New Zealand has increased cooperation with Thailand in many 
fields such as trade, investment, and tourism. Foreign Minister 
Prasong asked New Zealand to open its market to Thai goods. 
Thailand's trade with New Zealand amounts to 1,700 million baht 
at present with Thailand suffering a trade deficit. 
  On ASEAN ministerial meeting in Bangkok in July, New Zealand 
has pledged to attend the meeting as it views the meeting as a 
significant event to maintain peace and stability in Asia and 
the Pacific region. 
  On the situation in Cambodia and Myanmar [Burma], the Thai 
foreign minister called for a political settlement in Cambodia. 
He informed the New Zealand minister about Thailand's intention 
to invite Myanmar to attend the ministerial meeting in Bangkok 
in July. 

</TEXT>

