<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA March 29 -- A high-level military 
delegation of Cambodia led by General Tie Banh and General Tea 
Chamrat, co-ministers of national defence, arrived here today, 
beginning an official visit to Vietnam as guest of Minister of 
National Defence Gen. Doan Khue. 
  The delegation was welcomed at the guest house of the 
Ministry of National Defence by Gen. Doan khue, Lt. Gen. Nguyen 
Thoi Bung, Deputy Minister of National Defence Nguyen Dinh Bin, 
Assistant to the Foreign Minister Pham Hao, vice president of 
the Vietnam-Cambodia friendship association, and other Vietnam 
senior officials. 
  Cambodian Charge d'Affaires to Vietnam I.E. Chuong Tuon, and 
Military Attache Nomsophat were also on hand. 
  Gen. Doan Khue warmly welcomed the visit and considered it a 
contribution to the enhancement of the friendly relations 
between the two countries and armies. 
  In the afternoon, the Cambodian delegation held talks with a 
high-level military delegation of Vietnam. The two sides 
compared noted on how to develop the close neighbourliness 
between the two countries on the basis of the principles stated 
in the Vietnam-Cambodia joint communiques dated on Jan. 25,1992 
and August, 1993 in the interests of the two peoples, and for 
peace and stability in the region. 
  This evening, Gen. Doan Khue gave a banquet in honour of the 
Cambodian guests. 

</TEXT>

