<H3> <TI>   U.S.-ROK 28 Mar `War Exercise' Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK3003045894 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0440 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK3003045894 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Acts Creating Tension" -- KCNA headline] </F>
  [Text] Pyongyang, March 30 (KCNA) -- The U.S. imperialists 
and the South Korean puppets staged a war exercise directed 
against the North of Korea on March 28, creating a strong 
electronic jamming in the air above Yongwol, Chunchon, Kongju 
and Oeyon Islet, according to military sources. 
  It involved overseas-based flying corps including 
nuclear-capable F-16 fighter-bombers plus fighter-bombers, 
assault planes and observation planes belonging to the U.S. 
Airforce in South Korea and the South Korean puppet Airforce, 
more than 300 in all. 
  An RC-135 strategic reconnaissance plane flew over the 
military demarcation line (MDL) area that day for photographing 
and electronic espionage on the whole areas of the North. 
  On the same day, formations of helicopter gunships and 
transport helicopters of the puppet army staged exercises for 
supporting ground units in an attack and airlifting in the air 
above Paju and Yonchon Counties, Kyonggi Province, while 105 mm 
artillery units fired scores of shells at an area adjacent to 
the Demilitarized Zone of the MDL. 
  The war moves of the U.S. imperialists and the South Korean 
puppets against the North are driving the situation of the 
Korean peninsula to the brink of war. 

</TEXT>

