<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Nation `Fortified' Against Sanctions, Missiles </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK3003043894 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0425 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK3003043894 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Invincibility of DPRK" -- KCNA headline] </F>
  [Text] Pyongyang, March 30 (KCNA) -- The U.S. imperialists 
are increasing their military threat to the Democratic People's 
Republic of Korea. But the U.S. bellicose elements are making a 
mistake. 
  Socialism of Korea is an invincible socialism which cannot 
be 
destroyed with anything. 
  The kernel of the invincibility of the DPRK is the great 
singlehearted unity of the leader, the party and the masses. 
The community of destiny, an integral whole of ideology and 
purpose in which ideology is one, and the destiny and weal and 
woe are shared by all -- this is the singlehearted unity of 
Korea. This singlehearted unity in which the leader, the party 
and the masses form a harmonious whole is a unity which is 
hardened like steel in a grim test. In March last year a 
touch-and-go crisis was created, which might trigger off a war 
any moment, due to the reckless war manoeuvres of the U.S. 
imperialists and the South Korean authorities. In a few days 
more than 1.5 million young people volunteered to the Korean 
People's Army. Five million youths and students vowed to defend 
their leader, their party and the socialist homeland with their 
lives, becoming 5 million rifles and 5 million bombs. Hundreds 
of thousands of veterans rose up like a giant, shouting "we will 
take charge of defence." The entire people effected a great 
upswing in socialist construction with a rifle in one hand and a 
sickle or a hammer in the other. This is the strength of 
singlehearted unity mightier than thousands of nuclear bombs. 
  With this singlehearted unity, the Korean people are afraid 
of nothing and have no unconquerable fortress. 
  The DPRK is invincible as it has a matchless army which has 
grown under the guidance of the great brilliant commander. 
  The People's Army is mighty Armed Forces with both modern 
offensive and defensive means. Each man of it is prepared to be 
the match for a hundred. He is an indomitable soldier with 
faith and will to defend with his life the leader, the party and 
the motherland under any circumstances. 
  The entire people are armed and the whole country is 
fortified in Korea. The Worker-Peasant Red Guards and Young Red 
Guards are fully ready for defending the country. The defence 
industry guarantees the military equipment needed for the 
defence of the country. 
  Though the imperialists put pressure upon Korea, threatening 
economic "sanctions", the independent national economy remains 
unshaken. This is another source of the invincibility of the 
DPRK. 
  The Korean people have lived and are prepared to live on 
rice 
produced by them, clothes produced by them and daily necessities 
produced by them. 
  The U.S. imperialists must not run wild. They may dispatch 6 
million troops, not 600,000, and may deploy much more formidable 
missiles than Patriot. But they cannot frighten the Korean 
people. 
  The United States must ponder over the matter. If one likes 
fire he is bound to get burnt. 

</TEXT>

