<H3> <TI>   Rally Held To Protest Patriot Deployment Plan </TI></H3>
<H4>   Plan Termed `Blatant Challenge' </H4>
<F P=102> SK2903152494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1514 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2903152494 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, March 29 (KCNA) -- Pyongyangites held a 
rally today bitterly denouncing the plan of the U.S. 
imperialists and the Kim Yong-sam group to deploy Patriot 
missiles in South Korea. 
  Paek Hak-yon, permanent vice-chairman of the Pyongyang 
Municipal People's Committee, and other speakers branded the 
planned deployment of Patriot missiles as a blatant challenge to 
the nation's desire for peace and denuclearisation of the Korean 
peninsula and an unpardonable act to exterminate the nation 
through a nuclear war by deliberately increasing the tension. 
  They declared they would not pardon the brigands who 
reversed 
the DPRK-U.S. joint statement and steps of simultaneous action 
agreed upon at the DPRK-U.S. contact in New York and are 
threatening the DPRK with "sanctions." 
  The Korean people are not frightened by any missile and the 
Team Spirit nuclear war game, they said, warning that the U.S. 
imperialists and the South Korean puppet clique must refrain 
from reckless war moves and other rash acts. 
  The speakers declared that the Korean people and the 
People's 
Army closely united around General Kim Chong-il, their supreme 
commander, will smash the aggressors at one blow if they dare 
provoke socialist Korea. 

</TEXT>

