<H3> <TI>   LDP Forms Project Team for DPRK Issue </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW3103073794 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 31 Mar 
94 Morning Edition p 2--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW3103073794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On 30 March, the Liberal Democratic Party [LDP] 
established an "emergency project team on Northeast Asian 
affairs," which is chaired by Policy Research Council Chairman 
Ryutaro Hashimoto, in a bid to deal with the international 
situation concerning possible sanctions against the DPRK (North 
Korea). From now on, the team plans to meet once a week to 
study from an independent standpoint what form Japan's crisis 
control should take. The project team intends to present 
emergency proposals to the government if the situation becomes 
more tense. 

