<H3> <TI>   Governor Ota To Petition Mondale on Base Issue </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW3103090594 Naha RYUKYU SHIMPO in Japanese 31 Mar 94 
Morning Edition p 2--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW3103090594 </F>
<F P=104>  Naha RYUKYU SHIMPO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Speaking at a news conference on 30 March, 
Governor's Office Director Takayama disclosed that Governor Ota 
plans to call on U.S. Ambassador to Japan Mondale, who is 
scheduled to visit Okinawa on 10 April, to settle three serious 
problems resulting from the existence of U.S. military bases on 
Okianawa which are: 1) return of Naha Port; 2) return of the 
Yomitan Auxiliary Airfield and the abolishment of parachute 
training; and 3) cancellation and abolishment of live-fire 
exercises across prefectural Highway 104. Ambassador Mondale is 
scheduled to pay a courtesy call on Governor Ota on 10 April. 
After receiving his courtesy visit, Governor Ota plans to 
petition him for the solution of those issues. 
  Director Takayama said: "The Okinawa Prefectural Office 
heartily welcomes Ambassador Mondale's visit. In fact, we would 
like to arrange a meeting with him aside from his courtesy call. 
However, since his itinerary is crammed, we want to call on him 
to solve the issues immediately after receiving his courtesy 
visit." 

</TEXT>

